cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on navigation tasks in real-world environments using deep reinforcement learning. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper leverages place recognition and deep learning techniques to generate compact image representations. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper uses deep reinforcement learning to learn control policies from a small amount of experience. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper addresses perception and decision-making problems in navigation tasks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper presents an interactive framework for training and deployment of navigation algorithms.
